    tool_output=ToolOutput(
        output="# FY2025 Segment Adjusted EBITDA by Segment\n\nBased on the reconciliation table for the **Year Ended December 31, 2025**, the Segment Adjusted EBITDA for each segment is:\n\n| Segment | FY2025 Segment Adjusted EBITDA |\n|---|---|\n| **Space** | **$653 million** |\n| **Connectivity** | **$7,168 million** |\n| **AI** | **$(1,237) million** |\n| **Total Reportable Segments** | **$6,584 million** |\n\n---\n\n## Reconciliation Table (Year Ended December 31, 2025)\n\nThe table below reconciles **Income (loss) from operations** (the most directly comparable GAAP measure) to **Segment Adjusted EBITDA**:\n\n| (in millions) | Space | Connectivity | AI | Total Reportable Segments |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| **Income (loss) from operations** | $(657) | $4,423 | $(6,355) | $(2,589) |\n| Add: Depreciation and amortization | 757 | 2,376 | 3,568 | 6,701 |\n| Add: Share-based compensation | 515 | 369 | 1,063 | 1,947 |\n| Add: Restructuring charges | — | — | 487 | 487 |\n| Add: Impairment | 38 | — | — | 38 |\n| **Segment Adjusted EBITDA** | **$653** | **$7,168** | **$(1,237)** | **$6,584** |\n\n---\n\n## How Segment Adjusted EBITDA Is Calculated\n\nPer the filing, **Segment Adjusted EBITDA** is defined as segment income (loss) from operations excluding:\n\n1. **Depreciation and amortization**\n2. **Share-based compensation**\n3. **Restructuring charges**\n4. **Impairment**\n\n### Worked Example — Space Segment (FY2025):\n- Income (loss) from operations: $(657)M\n- + Depreciation and amortization: $757M\n- + Share-based compensation: $515M\n- + Restructuring charges: $0M\n- + Impairment: $38M\n- = **Segment Adjusted EBITDA: $653M**\n\n### Worked Example — Connectivity Segment (FY2025):\n- Income from operations: $4,423M\n- + Depreciation and amortization: $2,376M\n- + Share-based compensation: $369M\n- + Restructuring charges: $0M\n- + Impairment: $0M\n- = **Segment Adjusted EBITDA: $7,168M**\n\n### Worked Example — AI Segment (FY2025):\n- Loss from operations: $(6,355)M\n- + Depreciation and amortization: $3,568M\n- + Share-based compensation: $1,063M\n- + Restructuring charges: $487M\n- + Impairment: $0M\n- = **Segment Adjusted EBITDA: $(1,237)M**\n\n---\n\n## Key Contextual Notes\n\n- **Space** Segment Adjusted EBITDA decreased by $501M year-over-year (from $1,154M in 2024 to $653M in 2025), primarily driven by accelerated investment in the Starship vehicle and launch facilities, partially offset by increased NASA CRS missions and a U.S. Department of War contract.\n- **Connectivity** Segment Adjusted EBITDA grew significantly (86.2% year-over-year), driven by subscriber growth, enterprise adoption, and network efficiency improvements via the Starlink constellation.\n- **AI** Segment Adjusted EBITDA decreased by $1,584M (from $347M in 2024 to $(1,237)M in 2025), reflecting the segment's earlier stage of development and heavy investments in cloud computing, data center infrastructure, and employee expenses. The company expects a multi-year investment horizon before sustained positive Segment Adjusted EBITDA.",
