    tool_output=ToolOutput(
        output="# Segment Definitions and Descriptions\n\n## Space Segment\n\n**Definition:** The Space segment designs, manufactures, and launches reusable rockets to provide high cadence, reliable, and affordable access to space at unprecedented scale.\n\n**Products and Services:**\n- **Falcon launch vehicles** (Falcon 9 and Falcon Heavy), composed of boosters (first stages), second stages, Merlin engines, and fairings—boosters, fairings, and Merlin engines are reusable\n- **Dragon spacecraft** for transporting astronauts, satellites, and other payloads\n- **Starship** (in development)—a fully reusable transportation system designed to carry crew, cargo, satellites, and data centers to Earth orbit, the Moon, Mars, and beyond\n\n**Revenue Categories:**\n- **Launch Services** (recognized at point in time)—customer launches\n- **Launch & Development** (recognized over time)—long-term government contracts\n\n**Key Note:** Space segment revenue only reflects customer launches and customer activities. Launches dedicated to deploying Starlink satellites are capitalized within the Connectivity segment, and the company expects to allocate significant launch capacity to the AI segment in the future. As a result, the Space segment has relatively lower revenue scale and growth compared to other segments, though it provides foundational strategic value.\n\n---\n\n## Connectivity Segment\n\n**Definition:** The Connectivity segment operates a worldwide high-speed, low-latency broadband data and communications network powered by over 9,600 Starlink broadband and mobile satellites in Low-Earth Orbit, delivering connectivity to millions of consumer, enterprise, and government customers across 164 countries, territories, and other markets.\n\n**Products and Services:**\n- **Starlink Consumer Broadband**—the world's largest and most advanced space-based internet broadband service, with median latency at approximately 25 milliseconds and median download speeds of 225 Mbps during peak hours for residential users (as of March 31, 2026)\n- **Starlink Mobile**—satellite-to-mobile texting and over-the-top voice services, serving approximately 7.4 million monthly unique devices across approximately 30 countries\n- **Enterprise & Government connectivity solutions**\n\n**Subscriber Metrics (as of March 31, 2026):**\n- Approximately 10.3 million Starlink Subscribers\n- Approximately 9,600 Starlink broadband and mobile satellites in orbit\n\n**Revenue Categories:**\n- **Consumer**\n- **Enterprise & Government**\n\nAll products revenue is attributable to the Connectivity segment.\n\n---\n\n## AI Segment\n\n**Definition:** The AI segment operates a highly vertically integrated AI platform spanning a frontier LLM, AI solutions for consumer and enterprise customers, a real-time information platform, and AI computational infrastructure.\n\n**Products and Services:**\n- **Grok**—a truth-seeking frontier large language model\n- **AI solutions for consumer and enterprise customers**\n- **X**—a real-time information, entertainment, and free speech platform\n- **AI computational infrastructure**, including terrestrial power and AI compute infrastructure, with plans for orbital AI compute satellite deployments\n\n**Revenue Categories:**\n- **Advertising** (primarily from X)\n- **AI Solutions & Infrastructure**\n\n**Background:** xAI was founded in 2023 and acquired by SpaceX in early 2026, becoming an integral pillar of the company's vertically integrated innovation engine. The segment is in an earlier stage of development, with the company planning to prioritize growth and investment to capture significant opportunities in AI applications and compute infrastructure.\n\n---\n\n## Segment Reporting Framework\n\nEffective Q1 2026, following the Mergers, the company's Chief Executive Officer (as Chief Operating Decision Maker) organizes the company, manages resource allocations, and measures performance among these three operating and reportable segments. The CODM assesses performance and allocates resources based on **segment income (loss) from operations**, comparing actual results to historical results and previously forecasted financial information. Prior period presentations conform to the current three-segment reporting structure.",
